      "patchset_number": 3,
      "line": 29,
      "message": "I compared vfModuleCreate2AndPauseOnFirstVfm.json with the \"instance\" part of vfmoduleCreate2AndetPauseRequestOnFirst.json.\nThere are 150 common lines, and few unexpected differences (unexpected by me, i mean):\n\n\"isUpgraded\": false -> removed in vfModuleCreate2AndPauseOnFirstVfm\nempty \"optionalGroupMembersMap\" -> removed in vfModuleCreate2AndPauseOnFirstVfm\n\"upgradedVFMSonsCounter\": 0 -> removed in vfModuleCreate2AndPauseOnFirstVfm\n\nCan you explain what in the test made those vanish? (or how did they went into the preset)\n\n-\n-\n-\n\n\nWhat I suggest is adding an assertion that vfmodules has undefined \"pauseInstantiation\", but \"vocg_1804_vf0..Vocg1804Vf..ocgapp_004..module-11cxunx\" that do have a `\"pauseInstantiation\": \"afterCompletion\"`.\n\nI believe this can replace the whole \"deepCompare\", but this is my opinion.",
